  "prompt": "My father coming from kanpur on nanded got 6:30 hr late and now no where to go as he has to come to bti on punjab mail. Who is responsible for that?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about the delay your father is experiencing. In cases of train delays, a number of factors may be responsible, including technical issues, weather conditions, or operational challenges. Typically, the railway authorities are responsible for managing train schedules and ensuring timely service, but they may not always be able to control the specific causes of delays.\n\nIf your father is waiting for a connecting train, he can check with railway staff at the station for options. Additionally, he may want to contact the railway's customer service for further assistance or to file a complaint regarding the delay. If he has incurred additional expenses or inconveniences due to the delay, he may also want to inquire about compensation policies.",
